Day 15:
Step 0: 


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


1. Azure Logic Apps connect to Firewall:

Step 1: Create a Storage Account:
Step 1.1: You can search STORAGE ACCOUNTS in Search bar.
Step 1.2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Storage Accounts name
        b. Performance - Standard
        c. Region
        d. Performance
        e. Access Tier - hot
Step 1.3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review+create.
Step 1.4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Storage Account.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 2: Create two Logic Apps:
Step 2.1: You can search LOGIC APP in Search bar.
Step 2.2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Logic App name
        b. Subscription
        c. Region
Step 2.3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review + create.
Step 2.4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Logic App.
Step 2.5: Repeat the steps from 1-4 for creating Logic App 2.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 3: Create a Container:
Step 3.1: Go to the Containers that is located in the Storage Account you created.
Step 3.2: Click on "+CONTAINER" to add a new Container.
Step 3.3: Enter the details:
        a. Name
        b. Advanced if required
Step 3.4: Then click on OK to add a new Container,

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 4: Go to Logic App Designer and click on add trigger to add the following in your logic app:
      a. Azure Blob Storage: When a Blob is added or modified.
      b. Azure Blob Storage: Get Blob content.
Step 5: Then for testing click on RUN in Logic App's Overview page.

Step 6: Now, go to Networkings in Storage Account and enable Firewalls and Virtual Networks for protection.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 7: Go to Containers and try adding/Uploading a new file to your Container for TESTING FIREWALL.

